Ana Figueroa has spoken out for the first time since her son Nicholas died in a gas explosion on New York City's 2nd Avenue on March 26 . 
  Nicholas was on a blind date at a sushi bar when he was killed in the blast that destroyed three buildings . 
  Her family says that neither the landlord of the building nor Mayor Bill de Blasio have reached out to them with condolences . 
  The family has set up a memorial to Nicholas at the site of the explosion . 
  Nicholas' mother said that she still cries every night and that she wants justice for her son . 
 